A man has been arrested on a train in relation to an incident where an 86-year-old man was bashed and robbed in a shopping centre car park after taking his pension money out at an ATM.

Frank Carlino was captured on CCTV cameras walking with a cane through an underground car park on Frost Street at Chester Hill  in Sydney's west on Wednesday at 9.45am.

Police arrested a man after 11am on Thursday after footage, obtained by Nine News, showed a male punching Mr Carlino in the face after his female accomplice allegedly distracted him by asking if he needed a lift home.

